## Wire Formats

### Common Copilot headers (both formats)

  Authorization: Bearer <copilot_token>
  Content-Type: application/json
  User-Agent: GitHubCopilotChat/0.35.0
  Editor-Version: vscode/1.107.0
  Editor-Plugin-Version: copilot-chat/0.35.0
  Copilot-Integration-Id: vscode-chat
  X-Initiator: user   (when last message is from user)
              agent   (when last message is from assistant/tool)
  Openai-Intent: conversation-edits

### Format A: OpenAI Completions (gpt-4o, gpt-4.1, ...)

Implemented first — free-tier Copilot models use this format.
Free models confirmed (cost={input:0,output:0} in pi's model table):
  gpt-4o    — 64K context, 16K output, compat: supportsStore=false,
              supportsDeveloperRole=false, supportsReasoningEffort=false
  gpt-4.1   — same compat flags, 128K context

  POST https://api.individual.githubcopilot.com/chat/completions

Request body:
  {
    "model": "gpt-4o",
    "max_completion_tokens": 16384,
    "stream": true,
    "messages": [
      {"role": "system", "content": "<system prompt>"},
      {"role": "user",   "content": "<message>"},
      ...
    ],
    "tools": [ { "type": "function", "function": { "name": "exec",
      "parameters": { "type":"object", "properties": { ... } } } } ]
  }

Copilot compat (applies to all github-copilot OpenAI Completions models):
  "store" field: omit (supportsStore=false)
  System role: "system" not "developer" (supportsDeveloperRole=false)
  Max tokens field: "max_completion_tokens" not "max_tokens"
  reasoning_effort: omit (supportsReasoningEffort=false)
  Assistant message content: must be a plain string, never an array
    (Copilot rejects array content on assistant messages)

SSE response:
  data: {"choices":[{"delta":{"content":"text chunk"},"finish_reason":null}]}
  data: {"choices":[{"delta":{},"finish_reason":"stop"}]}
  data: [DONE]

Tool call SSE:
  data: {"choices":[{"delta":{"tool_calls":[{"index":0,"id":"call_abc",
         "function":{"name":"exec","arguments":""}}]}}]}
  data: {"choices":[{"delta":{"tool_calls":[{"index":0,
         "function":{"arguments":"{\"argv\":[\"ls\"]}"}}]}}]}
  data: {"choices":[{"delta":{},"finish_reason":"tool_calls"}]}

Arguments accumulate across chunks into a JSON string; parse when
finish_reason="tool_calls".  The arguments string is itself JSON:
  {"argv":["ls","-l"],"stdin":""}

Tool result for next request:
  {"role":"tool","tool_call_id":"call_abc","content":"<output>"}

### Format B: Anthropic Messages (all Claude models)

  POST https://api.individual.githubcopilot.com/v1/messages

Request body:
  {
    "model": "claude-sonnet-4.5",
    "max_tokens": 32000,
    "stream": true,
    "system": "<system prompt>",
    "messages": [ ... ],
    "tools": [ { "name": "exec", "input_schema": { ... } } ]
  }

Tool definitions use "input_schema" not "parameters".
No anthropic-version or anthropic-beta headers (Copilot proxy adds them).

SSE response — event:/data: pairs:
  event: content_block_start
  data: {"type":"content_block_start","content_block":{"type":"text"}}

  event: content_block_delta
  data: {"type":"content_block_delta","delta":{"type":"text_delta","text":"chunk"}}

  event: content_block_delta
  data: {"type":"content_block_delta","delta":{"type":"thinking_delta","thinking":"..."}}

  event: content_block_stop

  event: message_delta
  data: {"type":"message_delta","delta":{"stop_reason":"end_turn"}}

  event: message_stop

Tool call in SSE:
  content_block_start: content_block.type="tool_use", id="toolu_01...", name="exec"
  content_block_delta: delta.type="input_json_delta", partial_json="..."  (many)
  content_block_stop:  parse accumulated input JSON → {"argv":[...],"stdin":"..."}

Tool result (appended to messages as a user message):
  {"role":"user","content":[{
    "type":"tool_result",
    "tool_use_id":"toolu_01...",
    "content":"<output>",
    "is_error": false
  }]}

